diff --git a/.workflow/improve_log.md b/.workflow/improve_log.md
index 3422de0..15d1837 100644
--- a/.workflow/improve_log.md
+++ b/.workflow/improve_log.md
@@ -106,4 +106,10 @@
 - **Fix TurboPepper boost broken (boostInitialMultiplier missing)**: `activateTurboPepper` in items.js set `boostMultiplier = 1.45` but never set `boostInitialMultiplier`. The linear decay formula in kart.js (`1 + (boostInitialMultiplier - 1) * t`) immediately computed `1 + (1-1)*t = 1.0`, making the turbo pepper item completely ineffective — the speed boost vanished on the first frame. Added `kart.boostInitialMultiplier = 1.45` to the function. Verified: after one frame of decay, multiplier stays at 1.445 instead of dropping to 1.0.
 - **Fix shield visual mesh leak on re-activation**: `activateShield` always created a new `shieldBubble` child mesh without checking if one already existed. If a kart activated a second shield (from item pickup while already shielded), two overlapping sphere meshes accumulated — the first was never removed since `removeShieldVisual` only finds the first match via `getObjectByName`. Added a guard that calls `removeShieldVisual()` before creating the new bubble if `shieldActive` is already true.
 - **Fix stale state leak on quit-to-menu**: After quitting, `raceState.status` remained `'racing'`, `window.__allKarts` pointed to the old 8-element array (since `allKarts = []` creates a new reference), and `window.__trackData` held the old track data. Any code checking these after quit would see stale data. Now `quitToMenu()` resets `raceState.status = 'pre'` and all related fields, and nullifies the debug window references.
-- Verified: pass — TurboPepper boost decays correctly (1.445 after one frame vs 1.0 before fix). State cleanup confirmed: `allKarts=null, trackData=null, raceStatus=pre` after every quit. Zero console errors across all 4 tracks (Sunset Bay, Mossy Canyon, Neon Grid, Volcano Peak) through full lifecycle: menu → select → countdown → race → quit → repeat.
\ No newline at end of file
+- Verified: pass — TurboPepper boost decays correctly (1.445 after one frame vs 1.0 before fix). State cleanup confirmed: `allKarts=null, trackData=null, raceStatus=pre` after every quit. Zero console errors across all 4 tracks (Sunset Bay, Mossy Canyon, Neon Grid, Volcano Peak) through full lifecycle: menu → select → countdown → race → quit → repeat.
+
+## Iteration 17 — Focus: Driving Feel
+- **Braking nose-dip visual feedback**: When the player brakes while moving forward (speed > 3), the kart mesh now pitches forward up to 0.18 radians (~10°) proportional to speed/topSpeed. The pitch lerps at rate 12/s for snappy response and decays smoothly when braking stops. This gives immediate visual weight-transfer feedback — you can see the kart "nose down" under hard braking, making it feel physical. Tested: pitch peaks at 0.116 rad at speed 80, decaying through 0.034 at speed 7.
+- **Off-road visual bounce**: Per spec requirement ("kart bounces slightly more" on off-road), added a sinusoidal Y-axis bob to the kart mesh when `surfaceBlend > 0.1` and speed > 8. Bounce frequency scales with speed (6 + speed×0.12 Hz) and amplitude scales with both surfaceBlend and speed ratio (max ±0.25 units). The bob phase accumulator is bounded to prevent float precision drift over long races. Bob resets on respawn.
+- **Speed-dependent camera FOV**: Camera FOV now modulates with kart speed for a "speed rush" effect. At standstill: 63° (slightly narrower, intimate feel). At top speed: ~71.5°. During boost overspeed (up to 1.4× top speed): up to ~75°. The FOV lerps smoothly (factor 0.1^dt) to avoid jarring snaps. Combined with the existing speed-dependent chase distance, this creates a convincing sense of acceleration. The projection matrix is updated each visual frame.
+- Verified: pass — Zero console errors on all 4 tracks (Sunset Bay, Mossy Canyon, Neon Grid, Volcano Peak). All 8 karts racing on every track. Brake pitch confirmed active (0.116 rad peak). No NaN values on any kart property. Properties (pitchAngle, offroadBobPhase) correctly initialized and reset on respawn.
\ No newline at end of file
